Challenges Across Paradigms: Standardization/reproducibility of complex mixtures, translational gaps (bench-to-clinic), intellectual property/benefit-sharing, and funding competition with synthetic/biologic approaches.
Doctoral-level work often operates at the intersections (e.g., ethnopharmacology + metabolomics + network analysis). The dominant contemporary paradigm is hybrid and translational: leveraging traditional knowledge and evolutionary-optimized chemistry with cutting-edge tools for discovery, validation, and sustainable application. 

